article.headline: Balanced Rockets place seven in double-figures
article.linkText: Francis' 12 asssists help Rockets beat Nuggets
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Steve Francis did a good job of quarterbacking a balanced offense.
Francis

Francis had 18 points and tied his season high with 12 assists as the Houston Rockets had seven players in double figures in a 102-89 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Saturday night. "I thought we had good ball movement,'' acting coach Larry Smith said. "We swung it to the open guy and got 24 assists. Everyone came in and contributed well. We made plays late when it was crunch time and made stops when we were supposed to.'' The Rockets led 81-68 at the start of the fourth quarter, but the Nuggets got the lead down to 89-85 with 3:36 to play. Maurice Taylor then hit a jumper, Francis scored on a fast break and Taylor added a three-point play for a 96-85 lead with 2:07 to go. Taylor had nine of his 15 points in the fourth quarter. Kelvin Cato added 14 points and six blocked shots. Yao Ming had 11 points and two rebounds. "Steve and the rest of the guys put me in a position to shoot the basketball going toward the basket,'' Cato said. "If we could do that every night, I would score more. I tried to keep aggressive and keep getting rebounds.'' Yao played only 15 minutes and was slowed by four fouls. Yao said he expected Cato's performance. "Why should I be surprised? That's the way he plays. He just doesn't get that many opportunities,'' Yao said. The Nuggets dropped to 4-33 on the road, the second worst road record in the NBA. Marcus Camby led the Nuggets with 18 points and 15 rebounds and Nene Hilario added 17 points. "It was back and forth in the third quarter,'' Camby said. "Then they opened up the big lead. We battled it back down to four but we just couldn't get over the hump.'' After trailing 51-46 at the half, Denver had a 12-5 run to start the third quarter and took its first lead since the first period, 58-56, with Camby and Nene Hilario each getting four points in the run. "It was tough at times tonight,'' Francis said. "We were just trying to get everybody involved. This was one of the best complete games we've played. It's the first time we got seven guys in double figures and I thought that was big for us.'' The Rockets came back with a 25-10 charge to end the period with an 81-68 lead. Camby hit the first basket of the game and had eight first-quarter points to get the Nuggets the early lead, but they lost it in a 14-4 Rockets run for a 27-25 lead at the end of the first period. "Francis made some big shots down the stretch,'' Camby said. "He would get in the lane and either make a shot or he would draw me to him and dish the ball either to Cato or to someone else. He was effective down the stretch as he always is.'' James Posey, obtained from Denver on Dec. 18, scored 16 points against the Rockets before the trade and 18 points against the Nuggets after the trade. He finished with 11 points, four assists and five rebounds. "Marcus did a heck of a job,'' Nuggets coach Jeff Bzdelik said. "He was very effective. He had 18 points and 15 rebounds. That's a great night.''

Game notes
Houston F Bostjan Nachbar, currently on the injured list, and Denver's Nikoloz Tskitishvili were teammates for Benetton Treviso in Italy last season. ... Juwan Howard needs four steals to reach 600 for his career. Howard sat out the game with the flu.
